config BR2_PACKAGE_SEED_ENTROPY
	bool "seed-entropy"
	help
	  Native saved-seed lifecycle helper. It atomically consumes a
	  single-use persistent seed, mixes it through the kernel write path,
	  credits it separately with RNDADDENTROPY, and durably rotates a
	  replacement without permitting replay or same-boot circular credit.
	  Transactional boot-epoch and SHA-256 markers bind provenance to the
	  exact generated seed until a later boot.

	  Its separate shutdown initializer only creates the first seed after
	  an in-process CRNG readiness proof. Markerless seeds from older
	  releases are mixed without credit and regenerated. Unsafe paths,
	  metadata, device identity, partial lifecycle states, and concurrent
	  invocations fail closed.

	  https://d-central.tech/
